'''热休克蛋白'''（{{lang-en|Heat shock proteins}}，又称'''热激蛋白'''，简称为'''HSP'''）是一类功能性相关[[蛋白质|蛋白质]]，当[[细胞|细胞]]受到升高温度或其他胁迫时它们的表达就会增长<ref name="pmid9921710">{{cite journal | author = De Maio A | title = Heat shock proteins: facts, thoughts, and dreams | journal = Shock (Augusta, Ga.) | volume = 11 | issue = 1 | pages = 1–12 | pmid = 9921710 | doi = 10.1097/00024382-199901000-00001| url = | issn = |date=January 1999}}</ref>，可協助蛋白質正常[[蛋白質摺疊|摺疊]]。这种表达的增长是受到[[转录|转录]]调控的。热休克蛋白大幅上调控是'''热休克反应'''的关键部分并且主要由[[热休克因子|热休克因子]]引导<ref name="pmid8689565">{{cite journal | author = Wu C | title = Heat shock transcription factors: structure and regulation | journal = Annual review of cell and developmental biology | volume = 11 | issue = | pages = 441–69 | year = 1995 | pmid = 8689565 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.cb.11.110195.002301 | url =  }}</ref>。在从[[细菌|细菌]]到[[人类|人类]]的几乎所有生物中都发现了热休克蛋白。

热休克蛋白的命名是依据他们的分子质量。例如，Hsp60、Hsp70与Hsp90（被研究最多的热休克蛋白）指的是热休克蛋白家族的尺寸分别大约60、70与90[[原子质量单位|千道尔顿]]<ref name="pmid18432918">{{cite journal | author = Li Z, Srivastava P | title = Heat-shock proteins | journal = Current protocols in immunology / edited by John E. Coligan ... [et al.] | volume = Appendix 1 | issue = | pages = Appendix 1T | pmid = 18432918 | doi = 10.1002/0471142735.ima01ts58 | url =  |date=February 2004}}</ref>。小到8千道尔顿的蛋白[[泛素|泛素]]，这种蛋白用于标记即将分解的蛋白质，也表现出热休克蛋白的性质<ref name="pmid1668897">{{cite journal | author = Raboy B, Sharon G, Parag HA, Shochat Y, Kulka RG | title = Effect of stress on protein degradation: role of the ubiquitin system | journal = Acta biologica Hungarica | volume = 42 | issue = 1-3 | pages = 3–20 | year = 1991 | pmid = 1668897 | doi = | url = | issn = }}</ref>。

== 功能 ==
熱休克蛋白最為人所知的功能為幫助蛋白質的摺疊。此外，熱休克蛋白也可以調節細胞膜的形變。比利時的研究團隊發現熱休克白90（Hsp90）可以幫助胞膜形變，誘導[[外吐小體|外吐小體]] 釋放<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Hsp90 Mediates Membrane Deformation and Exosome Release|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1097276518305859|date=2018-09-06|journal=Molecular Cell|issue=5|doi=10.1016/j.molcel.2018.07.016|volume=71|pages=689–702.e9|language=en|issn=1097-2765}}</ref>。

